LinkedIn says the 996 work schedule is “taking over” the U.S. — you know, 9am to 9pm, 6 days a week. Reality check: it’s not. It’s just San Francisco tech bros and AI startups cosplaying hustle culture.

CEOs are bragging about answering emails at 1am like it’s a flex. AI companies fire you, rehire you, and then expect you to work 72-hour weeks for the same salary. Unless you own the company, 996 is just free labor with extra steps.
